cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset or code, please cite the accompanying paper."
title: "Reproduction Database — When the Thinking Mode Strengthens the Anchor: Authority-Rationalized Anchoring in LLM Legal Judgment"
abstract: >-
  Data, analysis code, prompts, and figures reproducing every table and figure in
  the paper. Toggling thinking mode on/off across seven deployed LLMs on a Chinese
  civil personal-injury damages task, adoption of an authority-tagged numerical
  anchor changes monotonically with source credibility; three vendors' models cross
  zero (thinking debiases a fortune-teller anchor and amplifies a chief-judge anchor).
authors:
  - name: "Anonymized for double-blind review"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - anchoring bias
  - reasoning / test-time thinking
  - legal judgment
  - authority bias
license: MIT
date-released: 2026-06-21
